formThreeBId.notesToCertificate:
1.)Current project under registration this is not new registration it is sub division of the previous registration vide
reg . no. PR/GJ/GANDHINAGAR/GANDHINAGAR/Others/MAA00503/A1M/EX1/260619. Thus during issue of certificate we have
taken few assumptions to come to final withdrawal figures:
1.Land cost, common construction cost and other common expenditure are allocated in the proportion of the respective carpet
area of Phase I and Phase II. (Phase I will have 128 units having carpet area of 4238.13Sq Mtrs and Phase II having 201 units
with 9521.25 SqMtrs of carpet area)
2.Phase specific cost are taken in the respective phases.3.The assumptions for allocation of expenses and specific cost are provided by promoters, we have verified the allocation on test check basis.
4.Estimated cost is provided by promoters of the project.
5.As this is sub division of the project and few units are booked in phase I and at the time of registration of Phase II or splitting of
the project the same units are transferred to the Phase II the collection there of is routed in Phase I RERA account. To avoid
ambiguity with respect to routing of booking amount through RERA account we are considering 100% consideration received
from members in point no. 7 instead of 70% which will reduce overall eligible withdrawal amount.
2.)It is not possible for us to very phone numbers produced before us by doing individual calling. Thus we have relied on the
information provided by the promoters.3.) We have verified information based on the books of accounts and other evidence
produced before us. We could able to comment on financial transaction only for other information we have relied on information
produced by the promoter of the project. We do not have competence to comment on the carpet area and other measurement
mentioned in the certificate. For the same we have relied on the information produce by the management/promoter of the project.
4.) Technical data as to measurement and others are taken as provided by the Architect and Engineer to the management.
5. )Bank Balance are subject to reconciliation. Issued cheques which are not deposited or under clearing are considered as paid.
SimilarlyCheques received and not cleared are taken as received. Balance are verified and taken as per books of accounts.6) Estimated Cost For Form-2 is Reduced from 28,00,00,000 to 24,00,00,000 in Form-2.However we have Kept as it is. 7.)The cost incurred for the project as per engineer certificate vis a vis cost incurred on books of accounts is having major variation on seeking explanation from the promoter we came to know that few invoices are not received from the contractor due to covid-19 situation the same will be regularised in due course. However we have verified the site progress, the project is
progressing fast and will be completed far before completion date.
